<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>DutchNews.nl</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/</link><description>DutchNews.nl brings daily news from The Netherlands in English</description><lastBuildDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 10:03:47 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Ten killed in drugs labs explosions so far this year, say police</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/ten-killed-in-drugs-labs-explosions-so-far-this-year-say-police/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238661 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-drugs category-rotterdam"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Ten killed in drugs labs explosions so far this year, say police</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-25T10:03:47+00:00"> July 25, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-214784" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_214784"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="450" sizes="(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/drugslab-001cms.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/drugslab-001cms.jpg 800w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/drugslab-001cms-560x315.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/drugslab-001cms-768x432.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/drugslab-001cms-640x360.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/drugslab-001cms-92x52.jpg 92w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/drugslab-001cms-130x73.jpg 130w" width="800"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-214784"> One of the drugs labs. Photo: Politie.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Ten people have been killed and five injured in explosions and chemical leaks at drugs labs in the Netherlands and just over the border in Belgium so far this year, the <a href="https://www.telegraaf.nl/nieuws/1840364318/slaven-uit-buitenland-ingezet-in-drugslabs-tussen-woningen-dit-jaar-al-tien-doden-en-vijf-gewonden">Telegraaf reported</a> on Thursday, quoting police figures.</p><p>The police are particularly worried because more labs are being set up in the middle of residential areas, and are using “amateurs” and “foreign slaves” to produce the drugs, the paper said.</p><p>In February three people were killed in an explosion at a <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/02/rotterdam-blast-may-have-been-caused-by-drugs-lab-man-arrested/">drugs lab in Rotterdam</a> and two weeks later, one person was injured in a “massive” blast in Herveld in Gelderland. Three Dutch nationals were killed by toxic fumes in Poderlee, just over the Belgian border and another person was killed in a lab in Herwijnen.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The police are not commenting on the other three deaths because the investigation is still ongoing, the paper said.</p><p>Conflicts between drugs gangs have also led to the surge in firebomb attacks on private homes and businesses, the paper said. There were almost 500 in the first five months of this year.</p><p>Last year the police discovered <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/05/dutch-police-bust-more-drugs-labs-fewer-marijuana-plantations/">151 locations</a> where ecstasy, amphetamines and crystal meth were being produced, or heroin and cocaine were being processed. The east of the country is also replacing Noord Brabant as the centre of the illicit drugs trade.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>“We are extremely concerned about public safety,” police spokesman Willem Woelders told the paper. “This year we are on 10 deaths and five injuries in 13 major incidents. There is a clear trend.”</p><p>Former ecstasy producer Henk told the paper that the “good cooks” are now being replaced by amateurs.</p><p>“You can give an amateur a piece of paper with instructions but if things go wrong … they can’t take action because they don’t understand the process,” he said. “The smallest mistake can lead to explosions or poisonous fumes. And the labs often use slaves from abroad. It is simply human trafficking.”</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/drugs/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/rotterdam/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238661</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 10:03:47 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dutch royals should stick to ceremonial role, says Omtzigt</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/dutch-royals-should-stick-to-ceremonial-role-says-omtzigt/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238652 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-jobs category-nsc-2 category-royals category-royalty category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Dutch royals should stick to ceremonial role, says Omtzigt</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-25T09:23:20+00:00"> July 25, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-238653" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_238653"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="833" sizes="(max-width: 1250px) 100vw, 1250px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/zomerfotosessie-2024-koninklijk-gezin-paleis-huis-ten-bosch.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/zomerfotosessie-2024-koninklijk-gezin-paleis-huis-ten-bosch.jpg 1250w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/zomerfotosessie-2024-koninklijk-gezin-paleis-huis-ten-bosch-560x373.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/zomerfotosessie-2024-koninklijk-gezin-paleis-huis-ten-bosch-1200x800.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/zomerfotosessie-2024-koninklijk-gezin-paleis-huis-ten-bosch-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/zomerfotosessie-2024-koninklijk-gezin-paleis-huis-ten-bosch-768x512.jpg 768w" width="1250"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-238653"> The royals in front of their home. Photo: ©RVD - Patrick van Katwijk</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>The Dutch royal family would be better focusing on their <a href="https://www.royal-house.nl/members-royal-house/king-willem-alexander/position-and-role-as-head-of-state">ceremonial roles</a>, rather than being involved in more political issues such as the childcare benefit scandal, NSC leader Pieter Omtzigt has told <a href="https://www.ewmagazine.nl/nederland/achtergrond/2024/07/omtzigt-laat-leden-koninklijk-huis-zich-beperken-tot-kerntaken-1424234/">news magazine EW</a> in an interview.</p><p>Either members of the royal family limit themselves to their own, mainly ceremonial jobs, or an “exception is made to the rule that the prime minister is responsible for the actions of the royal household in appropriate cases,” Omtzigt told the magazine.</p><p>In the Netherlands, the prime minister is accountable for the actions of members of the royal household and has a weekly meeting with the king on government policy.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The NSC founder was responding to <a href="https://www.royal-house.nl/documents/speeches/2022/11/07/online-speech-queen-maxima-at-the-conference-towards-a-legislative-framework-enabling-a-digital-euro-for-citizens-and-businesses-europese-commission-and-the-european-central-bank">comments made by queen Máxima</a> about the advantages and disadvantages of the digital euro, and the role of princess <a href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/childcare-benefit-scandal-compensation-plan-will-go-ahead/">Laurentien’s foundation</a> in distributing compensation to childcare benefit scandal victims.</p><p>“If it transpires that the budget for using the Laurentien method is overspent, then prime minister Dick Schoof is responsible,” Omtzigt said. This means Schoof would, in effect, be responsible for something he has no control over.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>“It is high time we ensure that members of the royal house no longer do things besides their actual, ceremonial work,” he said. “For queen Máxima, this is even more sensitive than for princess Laurentien, who is somewhat further from the throne.”</p><p>Former prime minister Mark Rutte, Omtzigt said, was too lax in his dealings with the royals. Schoof told the Volkskrant that he did not which to react to Omzigt’s comments.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/jobs/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/nsc-2/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/royals/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/royalty/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238652</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 09:23:20 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>15 members of an ATM explosion gang are jailed in Germany</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/15-members-of-an-atm-explosion-gang-are-jailed-in-germany/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238650 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-banking category-crime category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> 15 members of an ATM explosion gang are jailed in Germany</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-25T08:34:23+00:00"> July 25, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-202131" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_202131"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1920" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-2048x1536.jpg 2048w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-640x480.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-83x62.jpg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/plofkraak-wikipedia-crop-130x98.jpg 130w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-202131"> Photo: Wikimedia Commons</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Fifteen predominately </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Dutch men</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> have been jailed for up to five years in Germany for blowing up ATMs.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The gang, based in the Netherlands, blew up some 30 cash machines in Germany between November 2021 and their arrests last year. In total, they are said to have stolen €3 million and caused damage put at €5.5 million.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The court ruled that 11 of the gang, aged 23 to 43, had been involved in the explosions and four were complicit. The verdict against a 16th man will be announced later. </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">In total, </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/04/dutch-nationals-blew-up-hundreds-of-german-atms-last-year/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">137 Dutch nationals</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> were arrested last year in connection with blowing up ATMs. In total they are suspected of causing 367 explosions at cash points, all but eight of which were in Germany.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The gangs are thought to have moved into Germany because of measures taken in the Netherlands </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">to better protect ATMs</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">. In some cases, for example, </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">bank notes</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> are automatically glued together in a blast.</span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/banking/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/crime/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238650</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 08:34:23 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Deaths by drowning rose to 139 last year, more foreign victims</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/deaths-by-drowning-rose-to-139-last-year-more-foreign-victims/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238638 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-accidents category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Deaths by drowning rose to 139 last year, more foreign victims</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-25T08:15:38+00:00"> July 25, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-107303" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_107303"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="667" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/swimming-river.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/swimming-river.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/swimming-river-360x240.jpg 360w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/swimming-river-560x374.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/swimming-river-768x512.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/swimming-river-300x200.jpg 300w" width="1000"/></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Last year 139 people drowned in the Netherlands, 41 of whom were on holiday or not officially registered as residents, national statistics office CBS has confirmed to Dutch News.</p><p>Most of them (75%) died in open water such as the sea or a lake, and most of the rest drowned at home, such as in a bath, garden pond or pool.</p><p>The figures, a sharp rise on 2022 and 2021, do not include suicide-related deaths by drowning.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Most of the victims were over the age of 60. Up to around 2000, young children accounted for by far the most victims, the CBS said.</p><p>Nevertheless, over the past 10 years, 64 children under the age of 10 and 50 aged 11 to 20 have drowned in the Netherlands, half of whom had foreign roots. Teenagers born outside Europe or with at least one non-European parent are 14 times more likely to drown than their Dutch peers.</p><p>Last week alone several people drowned in the sea or swimming lakes, including a 14-year-old Somalian boy.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/accidents/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238638</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 08:15:38 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>A cheese slicer is a cheese slicer is a cheese slicer: court</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/a-cheese-slicer-is-a-cheese-slicer-is-a-cheese-slicer-court/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238636 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-business category-court-cases category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> A cheese slicer is a cheese slicer is a cheese slicer: court</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-25T08:07:13+00:00"> July 25, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-238644" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_238644"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="556" sizes="(max-width: 716px) 100vw, 716px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/768px-Cheese_planes-e1721894697231.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/768px-Cheese_planes-e1721894697231.jpg 716w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/768px-Cheese_planes-e1721894697231-560x435.jpg 560w" width="716"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-238644"> A collection of cheese slicers. Photo: Chris Psi</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Supermarket chain Plus can continue to sell a cheese slicer from the Klaverland brand following a <a href="https://uitspraken.rechtspraak.nl/details?id=ECLI:NL:RBMNE:2024:4318">legal dispute</a> over its design with former supplier Boska Food Tools.</p><p>Boska argued that the new slicer looked virtually identical to the one it supplied to Plus until last year, when, after a cooperation of 16 years, the chain decided to go into business with Klaverland maker Morenso International.</p><p>Both Plus and Morenso were therefore in breach of its intellectual property rights, the manufacturer claimed.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The conflict started following Morenso’s<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/morenso-international_plussupermarkt-klaverland-kaasschaaf-activity-7142838480551813122-a28a/?originalSubdomain=nl"> presentation</a> of its products for Plus, <a href="https://www.rtl.nl/nieuws/economie/artikel/5462069/ruzie-kaasschaven-supermarkt-plus-auteursrecht">RTL Nieuws</a> reported, including a butter knife and a cheese grater, also almost indistinguishable from its own products.</p><blockquote class="twitter-tweet"><p dir="ltr" lang="nl">Rechter buigt zich over kaasschaafgeschil: lijken deze twee ontwerpen te veel op elkaar?<a href="https://t.co/MQfWopIIka">https://t.co/MQfWopIIka</a></p><p>— AD.nl (@ADnl) <a href="https://twitter.com/ADnl/status/1816169420852466015?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw">July 24, 2024</a></p></blockquote><p><script async="" charset="utf-8" src="https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js"></script></p><p>Morenso said it had not copied any of the Bosko products, arguing that the design of a cheese slicer is so “banal and trivial” it does not qualify for intellectual property right status.</p><p>The judge found for Morenso, saying “there are many cheese slicers, cheese graters and butter knives on the market which look a like the ones produced by Boska”. The manufacturer was ordered to pay costs.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/court-cases/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238636</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 08:07:13 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fire at Flevoland riding school kills 18 horses</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/fire-at-flevoland-riding-school-kills-18-horses/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238631 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-animal-welfare category-fire"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Fire at Flevoland riding school kills 18 horses</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-25T07:58:49+00:00"> July 25, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-238641" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_238641"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="649" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504141791.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504141791.jpg 1000w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504141791-560x363.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/ANP-504141791-768x498.jpg 768w" width="1000"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-238641"> Just two horses were rescued. Photo: LDG fotografie ANP</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>In total 18 horses have died in a fire at a riding school in Zeewolde in Flevoland in the early hours of Thursday morning.</p><p>The fire broke out shortly after midnight and spread quickly. Fire services managed to save just two of the horses, a spokesman told broadcaster NOS.</p><p>The stable, which housed the horses of several owners in the area, burned tot he ground but an adjacent building and house could be <a href="https://x.com/brandweerflevo/status/1816251435723460972">kept safe</a> from the blaze.</p><p>The fire may have started in the stable’s roof but its cause it still being investigated.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/animal-welfare/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/fire/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238631</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 07:58:49 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Hanneke Sanou]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>More cargo bike brands have breaking frames: RTL</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/more-cargo-bike-brands-have-breaking-frames-rtl/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238633 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-cycling category-society"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> More cargo bike brands have breaking frames: RTL</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-25T07:32:05+00:00"> July 25, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-231566" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_231566"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1512" sizes="(max-width: 2016px) 100vw, 2016px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Babboe-city-cargo-bike.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Babboe-city-cargo-bike.jpg 2016w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Babboe-city-cargo-bike-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Babboe-city-cargo-bike-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Babboe-city-cargo-bike-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Babboe-city-cargo-bike-1536x1152.jpg 1536w" width="2016"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-231566"> A Babboe City cargo bike. Photo: Dutch News</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The Dutch product safety board has confirmed it has received reports about problems with cargo bikes from brands other than Babboe and is looking into them, RTL said on Thursday.</span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">The problems </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">centre</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> on the welded frames, which break in the middle. The NVWA, which has decided to say which brands are involved, has sent inspectors to visit several owners, RTL said. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">“It is </span><span data-preserver-spaces="true">extremely important</span><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> that people report dangerous incidents which happen to them,” a spokesman said. The agency has had over 100 reports so far this year. </span></p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">Thousands of Babboe bikes have </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/06/babboe-recall-hits-the-skids-only-500-bikes-replaced-so-far/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">already been recalled</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> because of problems that emerged last year. In February the company was ordered to stop selling its cargo bikes because of the safety risks. </span></p><p><span data-preserver-spaces="true">In March, the NVWA began a </span><a class="editor-rtfLink" href="https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/03/nvwa-starts-criminal-investigation-into-babboe-cargo-bikes/" rel="noopener" target="_blank"><span data-preserver-spaces="true">criminal investigation</span></a><span data-preserver-spaces="true"> into the company after workers claimed they had been forced to cover up the problems. </span></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/cycling/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238633</guid><pubDate>Thu, 25 Jul 2024 07:32:05 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Tell us: have you managed to find an affordable place to rent?</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/tell-us-have-you-managed-to-find-an-affordable-place-to-rent/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238616 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-housing category-rental-housing newsletter-top-article"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Tell us: have you managed to find an affordable place to rent?</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-24T14:00:39+00:00"> July 24, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-195949" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_195949"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="480" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/IMG_90101.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/IMG_90101.jpg 640w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/IMG_90101-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/IMG_90101-83x62.jpg 83w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/IMG_90101-130x98.jpg 130w" width="640"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-195949"> Photo: DutchNews.nl</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Are you finding it difficult to rent a home in the Netherlands or are you paying a lot of money for a tiny room? We’d like to hear about your thoughts and experiences for a future article.</p><p>We know that there is a tremendous shortage of affordable places to rent and that even a room in a shared house can cost over €1,000. So how is this affecting your hunt for a home?</p><p>Are you a student facing “no internationals” signs or working for a startup and unable to find anything you can afford? Perhaps your employer helps pay your accommodation costs and is about to stop doing so? Or is your lease about to expire and you can’t find anywhere new to live?</p><p>Please tell us about your experiences by filling in the short survey below or by <a href="https://forms.gle/C5r1GgF7r7WWJV1Y9">clicking here</a>.</p><p><iframe frameborder="0" height="3307" marginheight="0" marginwidth="0" src="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSdEZcyoY_U7YOeSqeIT6NyKbvfM4qq3Htd0A1TZWmowaf7tIQ/viewform?embedded=true" width="600"><span class="mce_SELRES_start" data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;">﻿</span>Loading…</iframe></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/housing/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/rental-housing/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238616</guid><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 14:00:39 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>The Hague names bridges after Golden Earring and Pim Fortuyn</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/the-hague-names-bridges-after-golden-earring-and-pim-fortuyn/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238615 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-society category-the-hague"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> The Hague names bridges after Golden Earring and Pim Fortuyn</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-24T13:42:17+00:00"> July 24, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-238625" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_238625"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="1920" sizes="(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GD-golden-earringbrug-scaled.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GD-golden-earringbrug-scaled.jpg 2560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GD-golden-earringbrug-560x420.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GD-golden-earringbrug-1200x900.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GD-golden-earringbrug-768x576.jpg 768w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GD-golden-earringbrug-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2024/07/GD-golden-earringbrug-2048x1536.jpg 2048w" width="2560"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-238625"> Photo: Dutch News</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Rock band Golden Earring and assassinated politician Pim Fortuyn have had their names enshrined in two bridges near a park in The Hague.</p><p>The Pimfortuynbrug and Golden Earringbrug acquired their blue bordered name boards in May with no ceremony, after protracted efforts by the city council to agree on a suitable location.</p><p>Hart voor Den Haag, the populist party led by Richard de Mos, lauched a campaign in 2019 to name a street after Fortuyn, who was shot dead days before the 2002 general election.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>The council decided two years later to give his name to a bridge because of the controversy surrounding his anti-Islam views. “Not everyone wants to live in a Pim Fortuynstraat,” <a href="https://www.omroepwest.nl/nieuws/4499130/den-haag-vernoemt-brug-bij-zuiderpark-naar-pim-fortuyn">city alderman Hilbert Bredemeijer said at the time</a>.</p><p>The bridge crosses the Laakkanaal and connects the Zuiderpark to the multi-ethnic Transvaal district across Veluweplein. It is also close to the Meester P. Drooglever Fortuynweg, named after a former alderman in The Hague and mayor of Rotterdam in the first half of the 20th century.</p><p>The decision to honour Golden Earring was also taken in 2021 after the band announced they would stop touring when guitarist George Kooymans was diagnosed with motor neurone disease (ALS).</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Incontent"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_incontent-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Golden Earring were formed in The Hague in 1961 and are best known internationally for their hit Radar Love, but the band released 25 studio albums in their 60-year history.</p><p>Founder member Rinus Gerritsen said he had “no idea” that the bridge across Soesdijkseplein had been named after the band until he was asked about it by NOS on Tuesday.</p><p>“I’m really happy about it,” he said. “The fact that a bridge has been named after us means we’ve done something that moves people to do this sort of thing. And Soestdijkseplein is where we grew up.”</p><p><iframe allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" frameborder="0" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/aRlSHG5hRY4?si=SH7tXeUM2hZdHMEm" title="YouTube video player" width="560"></iframe></p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/society/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/the-hague/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238615</guid><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 13:42:17 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Gordon Darroch]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Zwolle drops plans to ban advertising for long distance flights</title><link>https://www.dutchnews.nl/2024/07/zwolle-drops-plans-to-ban-advertising-for-long-distance-flights/</link><description><![CDATA[<article class="post-238611 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-aviation category-business category-environment"><header class="pb-4 px-4"><h1 class="text-serif lh-1"> Zwolle drops plans to ban advertising for long distance flights</h1> <time class="text-secondary updated me-2" datetime="2024-07-24T13:05:07+00:00"> July 24, 2024 </time></header><figure aria-describedby="caption-attachment-50560" class="px-lg-5" id="attachment_50560"> <img alt="" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" height="2627" sizes="(max-width: 3503px) 100vw, 3503px" src="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CIMG3728.jpg" srcset="/wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CIMG3728.jpg 3503w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CIMG3728-560x419.jpg 560w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CIMG3728-1200x899.jpg 1200w, /wpcms/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/CIMG3728-300x224.jpg 300w" width="3503"/><figcaption class="px-4 px-lg-0" id="caption-attachment-50560"> Photo: Dutch News</figcaption></figure><main class="px-4"><p>Zwolle city council has abandoned its plans to ban outdoor advertising for airlines, cruises and other “products” which use fossil fuels because it is not legally possible, local broadcaster <a href="https://www.rtvoost.nl/nieuws/2454883/zwolle-gaat-reclame-voor-verre-vliegreizen-toch-niet-verbieden">Omroep Oost</a> said on Wednesday.</p><p>A majority of city councillors wanted to keep the adverts out of bus stops and off hoardings, but the plan is now on ice. This, officials say, is because it would conflict with freedom of speech rules and there was no clear definition of what the ban would cover.</p><p>The ban was due to have been enshrined in local bylaws, which cover local permits and licences. The city’s administrative board, however, has now decided against it. It is up to councillors if they want to pursue the idea.</p><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-none d-md-block"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden p-4 bg-light my-8 d-block d-md-none"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Inarticle"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_inarticle-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><p>Several Dutch cities have already taken steps to ban advertising for products that require the use of fossil fuels, such as travel and meat. Last year Utrecht voted to ban advertising for meat products from its own advertising hoardings at bus stops and the roadside, because of the impact on health and the climate.</p><p>The city had already banned “fossil fuel” adverts for petrol, cars and flying. Bloemendaal has also opted to stop advertising for meat, dairy and products that require fossil fuels and Haarlem, Tilburg, Wageningen, Amsterdam and the province of Noord-Holland are working on similar moves.</p><p>Advertising companies have said national rules would be preferable to a mish-mash of local initiatives and it will be up to the new government to decide what to do.</p></main><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-none d-md-block p-4 bg-light mt-8 mb-10 mx-lg-4"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><div class="ad-container overflow-hidden d-block d-md-none bg-light my-8"><div class="bg-light p-lg-2 h-100 w-100 d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center position-relative" data-tagname="ROS_Native"><div id="div-gpt-ad-dutchnews_ros_native-m" style="display:block;"></div></div></div><footer class="my-8 px-4"><div class="pb-8"></div> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/aviation/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/business/?list"></a> <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-sm" href="/category/environment/?list"></a></footer><div class="bg-green-light p-3 mx-4 mt-8 mb-12"></div></article>]]></description><guid>https://www.dutchnews.nl/?p=238611</guid><pubDate>Wed, 24 Jul 2024 13:05:07 -0000</pubDate><dc:creator><![CDATA[Robin Pascoe]]></dc:creator></item></channel></rss>